{
  "texts": [
    "The essence of precision medicine lies in tailoring treatments to the unique profiles of individual patients, which increases the complexity of handling diverse datasets.",
    "This challenge is particularly acute in oncology, where the lack of a universal therapeutic approach is acutely recognized.",
    "Tumor heterogeneity between patients and even within the same patient over time complicates the establishment of standardized treatments [130].",
    "The effective organization of biomedical data in biobanking infrastructures is crucial to enable a comprehensive approach to clinical studies as well as the development of AI tools supporting clinical decision-making [131,132].",
    "The main challenges are related to the (i) standardization, (ii) reproducibility and (iii) integration of data and procedures."
  ]
}